  "body": "Audit REST APIs for anywhere that we iterate through the entire validator list and use ValidatorUtil.getValidatorIndex\n\nfrom Adrian: In ValidatorWithIndex it’s searching through the entire list of validators to find the index and it’s running through that for each requested validator. On MainNet with a couple of hundred thousand validators, that’s going to go very, very badly. ValidatorUtil.getValidatorIndex is able to find the validator index for you and will use caches to make it efficient whenever possible. We should probably audit our REST APIs for anywhere that we iterate through the entire validator list and try to avoid it - definitely avoid it if it’s O(n^2) or worse in the number of validators.",
